Wash and dry produce. Cut @zucchini{1%unit} into half-moons.

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{} in a hot large pan. Cook salmon, skin sides down, until
skin is crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. Flip; cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}
more.

Meanwhile, drizzle @cooking oil{} in a separate hot large pan. Add zucchini;
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly
browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> Move on to Step 3 while salmon and zucchini cook!

== Brown Sugar Bourbon & Pecan Sauce ==

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @pecans{1%ounce},
@Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning{10.8%g}, @butter{2%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp}.
Microwave until butter has melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir to combine.

== Jasmine Rice ==

Massage @microwaveable jasmine rice{1%unit} in package to break up grains;
partially open package. Microwave for ~{90%seconds}.

> Be careful, the pouch will be hot!

== To Serve ==

Spoon brown sugar bourbon and pecan sauce over salmon and serve with
zucchini and rice.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.